What's the possible hashtag of this image with the following caption: 'The holidays are coming & I have been dreaming up some new recipes that will WOW your family & friends like this Roasted Winter Squash & Ricotta drizzled with @buzznbloom â€˜s Mesquite Blossom Honey. {AD}

This recipe was inspired by the fact that Iâ€™m always at a loss for what to do with the bulbous end of a butternut squash! So, for this holiday season I decided to make those curvy ends the star!! I paired them with delicata squash rings, creamy homemade ricotta, herbs, & a drizzle of #buzznbloom â€™s Mesquite Blossom Honey. This dreamy honey has flavor notes of warm maple with white pepper & itâ€™s slight kick pairs perfectly with the roasted squash. 
Be sure to bookmark this image to save this recipe for the holidays!! .
Roasted Winter Squash & Ricotta with Mesquite Blossom Honey
2 large servings or 4 small servings

bulbous end of 1 butternut squash, peeled, seeds removed, sliced into half moons
1 delicata squash, sliced into rounds, seeds removed
2 tablespoons extra virgin olive oil
1/4 teaspoon pumpkin pie spice
1/2 teaspoon kosher salt
freshly cracked black pepper to taste
1/4 cup toasted pepitas
12 ounces ricotta, preferably homemade 
1/8 cup Buzz + Bloom Mesquite Blossom Honey
1/2 teaspoon thyme leaves
1/2 teaspoon Maldon salt 
freshly cracked black pepper and red pepper flakes to taste

Preheat oven to 400Â°F. 
Arrange the squash slices on a baking sheet, drizzle with olive oil & sprinkle with pumpkin pie spice, salt & black pepper. Roast in the oven for 30 minutes, turning once, until the squash is beginning to caramelize around the edges. 
Once the squash has roasted allow to cool slightly. Divide the ricotta among the desired amount of plates, spreading into a thin layer. Layer the roasted squash on top then drizzle with the Buzz + Bloom Mesquite Blossom Honey. Sprinkle with thyme leaves, Maldon salt, freshly cracked black pepper, & red pepper flakes. Serve immediately. 
Recipe note: Making your own ricotta at home is really easy, not to mention impressive. Click the link in our profile for our homemade ricotta recipe or go to: http://thismessisours.com/recipes/red-white-and-blue-dunk-slather-board/'.
